        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 12:47AM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 1247 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Dauphin Island, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coden, Alabama Port, Grand Bay, Bayou La Batre, and Dauphin Island.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
